  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Evelina A. S. Smith has learned that Caroline Weston did not return to her school at the close of vacation; she did not know of the anxiety caused by Lucia Weston&apos;s illness. Evelina A. S. Smith is willing to assist at the refreshment table at the fair if she is needed. A sewing circle is working in Hingham for the Boston fair. Mr. Philemon R. Russell gave a fine discourse on anti-slavery in Hingham&apos;s new town house, explaining sympathetically the position of the old organization. Mr. John Murray Spear had two meetings on capital punishment.</subfield>
